{
  "texts": [
    "This results in significant updates to network weights, making the network unstable.",
    "If the derivative is less than 1, the gradient update information decays exponentially with increasing layers, causing the vanishing gradient problem.",
    "This prevents the model from learning effectively from training data, even with prolonged training.",
    "Choosing the appropriate activation function can effectively alleviate the issues of gradients vanishing and exploding.",
    "If the derivative of the activation function is 1, there is no problem of gradients vanishing or exploding, and each layer of the network can update at the same rate."
  ]
}